arChildNodes.szComment: Questioned on the exile of Crane Tribe, Ealda is amused by a fellow barbarian's unfamiliarity (player).
Questioned on the exile of Crane Tribe, Ealda shares their history as "betrayers" with the player--an outsider.

Ealda shares the story of the betrayer of Crane Tribe--Nihlathak, voicing he assisted Baal on mount Arreat, dooming his kin.
Nihlathak - "nee-la-thawk"
Baal - "Beyl"

Ealda speaks to Crane Tribe losing all respect among the tribes after Nihlathak's betrayal.
Arreat - "a(r-r)e-aht"
Ealda closes her story, clarifying Crane Tribe is alone because the sins of their ancestor require them to be.
